<subSubSection pageId="702" pageNumber="703" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="702" pageNumber="703">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="702" pageNumber="703">This Holarctic subspecies ranges from eastern Siberia (Kataev et al. 2003: 384) to the Alaska-Yukon border along the Porcupine River. On this continent, the subspecies is known from extant specimens only from the type locality. It was cited as a dominant taxon in a late Pleistocene site in the Klondike region of Yukon Territory (Zazula et al. 2006: 265).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
